1112: Taken together, the evidence supports a clear conclusion: tirzepatide is one of the most eﬀective available
1113: agents for combined glycemic control and weight reduction in adults with type 2 diabetes, with a beneﬁt
1114: proﬁle that is quantitatively large, durable, and consistent across treatment stages. Its main limitation is not
1115: lack of eﬃcacy but tolerability and selection: the right patient can beneﬁt a great deal, while the wrong
1116: patient may stop because of gastrointestinal symptoms or may need a diﬀerent agent because of comorbid
1117: risk. For clinicians, the practical task is therefore less “does tirzepatide work?” and more “which adults with
1118: type 2 diabetes stand to gain more from its metabolic potency than they risk from its tolerability burden?”
1119: The SURPASS program makes that tradeoﬀ much easier to judge than it was a few years ago. 
