1082: pancreatitis, severe gastrointestinal disease, advanced retinopathy requiring treatment, and more
1083: advanced kidney disease were often absent from the pivotal populations. Most eﬃcacy trials were 40 to 52
1084: weeks, and although SURPASS-4 and CVOT extend the horizon, the long-term safety practicalities of
1085: sustained high-dose therapy in real-world multimorbidity still need reﬁnement. These are genuine evidence
1086: gaps, not just theoretical caveats. 
1087: The development program is also still moving. SURPASS-CVOT has now reported, materially strengthening
1088: cardiovascular safety assessment. Switch studies are becoming important because many patients are now
1089: already taking a GLP-1 receptor agonist before tirzepatide is considered. SURPASS-SWITCH, reported in
1090: 2026, found that switching from dulaglutide to tirzepatide produced greater glycemic and weight
1091: improvements than escalating dulaglutide. ClinicalTrials.gov also lists ongoing or recently active adult type
1092: 2 diabetes studies evaluating investigational tirzepatide doses, tirzepatide in adults with type 2 diabetes
1093: and overweight or obesity, and switch strategies from prior GLP-1 receptor agonist therapy to tirzepatide.
1094: Those studies should improve the evidence base for sequencing and for dose optimization beyond the
1095: original pivotal program. 
