 577: The population gradient in these trials is clinically important. Mean age rose from the mid-50s in SURPASS-1
 578: and -3 to the mid-60s in SURPASS-4 and CVOT; mean baseline HbA1c ranged from roughly 7.9% to 8.8%;
 579: mean body weight was about 86 kg to 95 kg; and mean diabetes duration rose from 4.7 years in
 580: monotherapy to 14 years in the basal-insulin intensiﬁcation setting. The program therefore covers early
 581: disease and late disease, but generalizability is weaker for people with prior pancreatitis, advanced diabetic
 582: retinopathy requiring treatment, severe gastrointestinal disease, or very advanced kidney disease, because
 583: such patients were often excluded or speciﬁcally cautioned against. 
